  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Capacity-building facility for industry, technology and innovation policy</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As a follow-up of the 2030 Agenda mandate and the recently
established Technology Facilitation Mechanism (TFM), this project aims at creating a capacity building facility (CBF) on industry- related aspects of the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) that will provide information and analysis on the state of industrial development and provide capacity building in the context of specific country/regional needs and policies. The proposed facility will further provide a venue for facilitating policy dialogue, for matchmaking, and for the fostering of a global community of practice among relevant stakeholders.
The facility will i) identify and assess technology needs, including in industrial cooperation, innovation and investment promotion, and in related capacity building activities; ii) help facilitate development, transfer and dissemination of relevant technologies for the achievement of the SDGs; and iii) further help fostering global relations between technology-related stakeholders within and among developing and developed countries.
Ultimately, the facility will be UNIDO&#x2019;s core contribution to the United Nations system-wide call for mandate-specific measures towards the implementation and advancement of the TFM, the main framework for a technology- and innovation-driven achievement of the 2030 Agenda and the SDGs. It is expected that the project will facilitate the future development of major capacity development and policy advisory support services to Member States...</narrative>
  </description>
